item.title: Im pregnant!
item.dc:creator: @T41 t4
item.description:
@T41 wrote:

[quote=“N00b1, post:20, topic:271265”][quote author=OnlyOneRule link=topic=357988.msg2734238#msg2734238 date=1238953561]
If you’re serious and if you want to be serious about it. The only people who are really going to be able to help you are your parents. Even if it’s going to cause a big argument and you are going to hate every single part of life because of them. In the end they will be the ones to disapline you and help you through it. If you don’t tell your parents about your situation, things will only get worse until your thoughts take you over. This will leave your mind under the same amount of stress as in the case where you do tell them. Sometimes people need to grow up and listen to the people who guide them. I’ve been there and it took me around 16 years to realise how important my parents are, and how well they have disaplined me.
[/quote]

i second that one, only in the last few years have i calmed down and actually looked back and realised that your parents don’t tell you to do stuff or “tell you off” because they enjoy it they discipline you because you’ve been a tard[/quote]
Second it, tell your parents - it is well worth it.
